      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study performed at nominal operating point; GCI_fine = 3.1% for NIH quantity of interest. Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence (p=1.97). Fine mesh (12.8M cells) used for all production runs. GCI reported as uncertainty bound on all NIH predictions. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level3",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments conducted in temperature-controlled laboratory (37±0.5°C) using bovine blood with hematocrit verified by microhematocrit centrifuge (±0.5%). Flow rates set by calibrated Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5% full scale). Rotational speed verified by optical tachometer (±5 RPM). All nine envelope boundary/midpoint combinations tested. Achieved Gradation 4, exceeding required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "NIH comparison across 27 test conditions (9 flow-speed combinations × 3 hematocrit levels). Mean absolute error 9.4%, maximum error 12.0%, both within acceptance criterion of ≤15%. Statistical equivalence test (TOST, α=0.05) passed for mean NIH. Prediction intervals from Monte Carlo UQ encompass all experimental measurements. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "Primary QOI is Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH, mg/dL), the clinically accepted metric for hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841. NIH is directly compared to the clinical threshold of 0.8 mg/dL. Secondary QOIs (wall shear stress distribution, scalar stress exposure) are mechanistically linked to NIH through the power-law hemolysis model. QOI chain from CFD output to clinical decision criterion is fully documented. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (NIST-traceable rapid-prototype impeller). Blood analog fluid properties match declared hematocrit envelope. All five nominal COU operating points are within the tested validation space; boundary points of the operating envelope are explicitly included in the validation dataset. Geometric, material, and operational similarity between validation and COU is formally documented in the validation plan. Achieved Gradation 4, exceeding required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals converged to 1e-8 for all equations (continuity, momentum, scalar transport) in all production runs. Convergence monitored via residual history and NIH monitor point; no oscillatory behavior observed. Round-off error estimated at 1e-12 relative, negligible compared to discretization error. Achieved Gradation 2 meets required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "CFD simulation workflow executed under documented standard operating procedure (SOP-CFD-VAD-003). Independent peer review of simulation setup (boundary conditions, mesh, solver settings) performed by second qualified engineer. Checklist-based review documented. No use errors identified during review. Achieved Gradation 2 meets required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level3",
      "rationale": "Steady-state RANS (SST k-ω) turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal pump flows (FDA round-robin, Hariharan et al. 2011). Newtonian blood rheology justified for shear rates > 100 s^-1 (confirmed throughout impeller region). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied with literature-derived constants; model-form uncertainty quantified via ±10% coefficient Monte Carlo. Model form assumptions documented and bounded within the declared operating envelope. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "All boundary conditions derived from calibrated experimental measurements: inlet flow rate from Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5%), rotational speed from optical tachometer (±5 RPM), blood viscosity from cone-and-plate rheometer at 37°C (±2%). Uncertainty in each input propagated through Monte Carlo (500 samples). Sensitivity analysis identifies inlet velocity profile as dominant uncertainty source. Input uncertainty bounds documented in the UQ report. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "Three independent batches of bovine blood used for hemolysis bench tests, each from a separate donor animal, with hematocrit adjusted to 35%, 40%, and 45% targets. Each operating point tested in triplicate (n=3 per condition). Inter-batch variability assessed (CV < 8% for NIH). Sample preparation protocol follows ASTM F1841. Achieved Gradation 3, exceeding required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
